Dele Ogunyemi, Warri THE Social Democratic Party, Delta State chapter, has called on the people of the state to pray for the quick recovery of Governor Ifeanyi Okowa and his wife, Edith, who tested positive for COVID-19 The SDP also prayed for the quick recovery of the Secretary to the State Government, Chiedu Ebie, and the Commissioner for Information, Mr. Charles Aniagwu, who also tested positive for coronavirus. State Chairman of SDP, Oke Idawene, expressed confidence that they would all defeat the coronavirus pandemic and come out triumphantly. Idawane, who is also the Chairman, Forum of Registered Political Parties, South South Zone, said he received the news of the COVID-19 status of the governor and his wife with sadness. Copyright PUNCH. All rights reserved. This material, and other digital content on this website, may not be reproduced, published, broadcast, rewritten or redistributed in whole or in part without prior express written permission from PUNCH. Contact:Â theeditor@punchng.com 